content.text:
I see! The progression note is being generated by the `ProgressionCalculator` when there's no previous workout data. The workout for Week 2 Day 1 was likely created before you completed Week 1 Day 1, so it has this note saved.

**The solution**: Delete the Week 2 workouts from localStorage so they get regenerated with the correct progression data from Week 1. 

Can you try refreshing the page or clearing the Week 2 in-progress workouts? The easiest way is to run this in your browser console:

```javascript
// Remove all Week 2+ in-progress workouts
let inProgress = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('liftlog_in_progress_workouts') || '[]');
inProgress = inProgress.filter(w => w.week === 1);
localStorage.setItem('liftlog_in_progress_workouts', JSON.stringify(inProgress));
location.reload();
```

This will clear all the Week 2 and Week 3 workouts that were pre-generated before you completed Week 1, and they'll be regenerated with the correct progression data when you click on them again.

